# Goal: manual-jog iSWAP transfer between an on-deck plate site and a
# calibrated off-deck handoff position. Needed because the STAR firmware
# atomics (iswap_get_plate / iswap_put_plate) refuse off-deck X and bare
# rotations near end stops lock the drive — this action encodes the
# known-good recipe (middle-Y rotation, traverse-Z descent, wider
# release open) that the standalone ``iswap-to-incubator`` script uses.
#
# ``calibration_name`` is looked up at goal time in the node's
# ``handoff.<name>.{x,y,z,plate_width,rotation,wrist}`` parameters so
# live tuning via ``ros2 param set`` takes effect on the next goal.
#
# ``on_deck_resource`` is a name in the pylabrobot deck tree
# (e.g. ``plate_carrier_01/site_0`` or the plate itself).
#
# Zero floats below mean "use the server default".
string calibration_name
string direction                  # "to_handoff" | "from_handoff"
string on_deck_resource
float32 plate_width               # 0 = use calibration's plate_width
float32 pickup_distance_from_top  # 0 = use default (18.0)
float32 safe_y                    # 0 = use default (450.0)
float32 traverse_z                # 0 = use default (280.0)
geometry_msgs/Vector3 handoff_offset  # runtime nudge of the off-deck endpoint
---
bool success
string message
---
uint8 stage                       # 1..6
string stage_name
